18: // ExpressionFilter is an access logging filter that evaluates configured
19: // symbolic Common Expression Language expressions to inform the decision
20: // to generate an access log.
21: message ExpressionFilter {
22:   // Expression that, when evaluated, will be used to filter access logs.
23:   // Expressions are based on the set of Envoy :ref:`attributes <arch_overview_attributes>`.
24:   // The provided expression must evaluate to true for logging (expression errors are considered false).
25:   // Examples:
26:   //
27:   // * ``response.code >= 400``
28:   // * ``(connection.mtls && request.headers['x-log-mtls'] == 'true') || request.url_path.contains('v1beta3')``
29:   string expression = 1;
